div(class="login")
    div(class="btn-group flow")
        div(class="btn flowgrid on", id="authorization-flow")
            p step 1
                i(class="fas fa-check-circle")
            h4 Authorization
        div(class="btn flowgrid off", id="ibmkey-flow")
            p step 2
                i(class="fas fa-check-circle")
            h4 IBM key
        div(class="btn flowgrid off", id="search-flow")
            p step 3
                i(class="fas fa-check-circle")
            h4 Select Accounts
        div(class="btn flowgrid off", id="citation-flow")
            p step 4
                i(class="fas fa-check-circle")
            h4 Cite

    div(class="login-background", id="authorization")
        h1 Authorization
        p You must authorize us to access your Twitter account in order to user the tool.
        div(class="login-instruction")
            p Frequently Asked Questions:
            a(href="https://twitter.com/i/flow/signup", target="_blank") How to create a Twitter account?
            a(href="documentation#what-we-do", target="_blank") How are my credentials handled?
        div(id="twitter-auth")
            a(class="btn btn-primary btn-block", target="_blank")
                img(src="img/twitter-sm-logo.png" width=18)
                | Twitter account

    div(class="login-background", id="ibmkey")
        h1 IBM personality insights
        p Please provide your IBM personality insights key, which is <u>DIFFERENT</u> than your IBM Cloud
            | (formerly known as Bluemix) credentials.
        div(class="login-instruction")
            p Frequently Asked Questions:
            a(href="documentation#access-watson", target="_blank") How do I access IBM Personality Insights?
            a(href="documentation#find-watson-credential", target="_blank") How can I get an IBM personality insights key
        div(id="bluemix-auth")
            input(id="bluemix-personality-apikey", type="password", class="form-control", placeholder="Personality Insights API Key")
            button(class="btn btn-primary pull-right", id="bluemix-pin-submit")
                img(src="img/bluemix-sm-logo.png" width=18)
                | Submit

    div(class="login-background", id="search")
        h1 Select Accounts
        p Please select two Twitter accounts that you want to compare.
        div(id="user-search", class="row")
            input(class="form-control", placeholder="screen name, or search User screen name with keywords...")
            button(class="btn btn-primary pull-right botometer-icon", data-toggle="tooltip", data-placement="right", title="OSoMe Botometer " +
            "checks how likely the account is to be a bot. Higher scores are more bot-like. Click to proceed.")
                img(src="img/botometer-sm-logo.png" width=18)
                | Bot Check
            div(class="prompt")
        div(id="brand-search", class="row")
            input(class="form-control", placeholder="screen name, or search User screen name with keywords...")
            button(class="btn btn-primary pull-right botometer-icon", data-toggle="tooltip", data-placement="right", title="OSoMe Botometer " +
            "checks how likely the account is to be a bot. Higher scores are more bot-like. Click to proceed.")
                img(src="img/botometer-sm-logo.png" width=18)
                | Bot Check
            div(class="prompt")
        div(class=row)
            button(id="analyze-btn", class="btn btn-primary btn-block") Start Analysis
        div(class="loading")
            img(src="img/bae_loading_md.gif")

    div(class="login-background", id="citation")
        h1 Please Cite
        p Please cite these works below if you are going to use our tool for published research.
        div(id="citation-content")
            p Yun, J. T., Pamuksuz, U., & Duff, B. R. L. (1819). Are we who we follow? Computationally analyzing
                | human personality and brand following on Twitter. International Journal of Advertising, 0(0), 1â€“18.
                | <a href="https://doi.org/10.1080/02650487.1819.1575106" target="_blank">
                | https://doi.org/10.1080/02650487.1819.1575106</a> (Access to a free pre-print version of the article
                | can be found <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/330542500_Are_we_who_we_follow_Computationally_analyzing_human_personality_and_brand_following_on_Twitter"
                | target="_blank">HERE</a>)
            p Yun, J. T., Vance, N., Wang, C., Troy, J., Marini, L., Booth, R., Nelson, T., Hetrick, A., Hodgekins, H. (1818).
                | The Social Media Macroscope. In Gateways 1818.
                | <a href="https://doi.org/10.6084/m9.figshare.6855269.v2" target="_blank">https://doi.org/10.6084/m9.figshare.6855269.v2</a>
            p Arnoux, Pierre-Hadrien, Anbang Xu, Neil Boyette, Jalal Mahmud, Rama Akkiraju, and Vibha Sinha.
                | <a href="https://aaai.org/ocs/index.php/ICWSM/ICWSM17/paper/view/15681" target="_blank">25 Tweets to
                | Know you: A New Model to Predict Personality with Social Media.</a> AAAI Publications, Eleventh
                | International AAAI Conference on Web and Social Media (1817): pp. 472-475.
            p <a href="https://console.bluemix.net/docs/services/personality-insights/references.html#references"
                | target="_blank">More Research References ...</a>
        div(class=row)
            button(id="see-result", class="btn btn-primary btn-block") See Result

